    "They are used to get a rapid overview or 'gist' of a scene and help to orient the viewer in their surroundings.",
    "• Focal eye movements: Come into play after the initial ambient phase and involve longer, more deliberate fixations.",
    "Focal eye movements are used for detailed examination of objects or features of interest within a scene.",
    "When analyzing eye-tracking data, conditions of testing must be taken into account.",
